{
  "stem": "7157.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And my mother-- we never really knew what happened to him, except later on we heard stories that he was shot kind of in the street and taken away and shot.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So at this point, my grandmother, Golde, joined us in Stanislawow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She was all alone, so she came to Stanislawow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And you asked about the Germans.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Well, once the Germans came in, one of the first things they did-- and we're now talking about October, so maybe it wasn't the first thing.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Again, I don't know the exact months.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But this date certainly stands out in my mind, because it's-- not because I remember the date, but it was a-- one of those horrible events that you know the date of.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "October 12th, 1941, the Germans rounded up all the Jews in the city.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And when I say rounded them up, they went through apartments and they literally pushed people out into the center of courts, like town courts.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And there they had trucks.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And they trucked all the Jews-- and we were part of this group-- to a cemetery nearby in-- right outside of-- right in Stanislawow.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And fortunately for us, we got there early.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So that when they put the people in the cemetery, we were-- because we were taken early, we were put way back.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "You know, the people that came later were in the front.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Anyway, that day they shot and killed 12,000 Jews of the 15,000 that were at that cemetery.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And I can-- again, it's hard to tell whether I remember this or I was told this, but I-- it's a vivid memory, so I must remember it.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Seeing the German eating a sandwich.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I was told later it was a ham sandwich.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
